File: internal/server/commands/context.go
Package: commands
Purpose: Bridge helper to extract root server runtime applications directly out of active Cobra execution trees.
Functions:
func AppFromCommand(cmd *cobra.Command) (*serverapp.App, error). Context unpacker. Forwards the internal command context block straight into the application state locator. Errors: propagated context lookup failures.

File: internal/server/commands/root.go
Package: commands
Purpose: Assembles the main server CLI command tree and links native terminal flags to explicit Viper configuration keys.
Functions:
func NewServerRootCommand(v *viper.Viper) (*cobra.Command, error). Component constructor. Provisions explicit String flags for configurations, addresses, database strings, and structural standalone paths for server-ca-key, device-ca-key, and device-ca-crt material. Sets up automated context interceptors via PersistentPreRunE blocks. Errors: lookup configuration flag mapping errors.
Security Constraints: Validates execution context boundaries and links standalone filesystem isolation vectors before launching target use-cases.

File: internal/server/commands/start.go
Package: commands
Purpose: Launches the main server runtime loop and prints active profile layouts to the text output console.
Functions:
func newStartCommand() *cobra.Command. Instantiates the start sub-tree handler. Resolves running application contexts, evaluates active certificate provisioning schemes, and maps running configurations straight into active runtime structures.
Security Constraints: Cleans logs to shield internal secrets while verifying absolute visibility over infrastructure keys.

File: internal/server/commands/stop.go
Package: commands
Purpose: Provides an explicit terminal command shortcut to execute memory-bound runtime teardown steps.
Functions:
func newStopCommand() *cobra.Command. Builds the cleanup sub-tree. Resolves parent process contexts and triggers structural thread terminations.
